  "translations": {
    "en": "The one seeking counsel's right is sincere advice with mercy and kindness. The counselor's right is gentleness and attentive listening. If right, praise Allah; if not, show compassion, do not accuse, know he erred, do not hold it against him unless deserving. There is no strength save in Allah. The elder's right is reverence for his age, honour for his precedence in Islam. Do not confront him in dispute or precede him. If he acts foolishly, bear it and honour him by Islam's right. The younger's right is compassion, teaching, pardoning, covering faults, kindness, and helping.",
